----------
RDF Lingua
----------

RDF as the web talking language.

Reasoning with rules described in RDF as
    rulename a ruleType.
    rulename lingua:premise conjunctionList.
    rulename lingua:conclusion conjunctionList.

and able to give proof explanations as
    rulename lingua:bindings substitutionList.

A ruleType is one of lingua:ForwardRule, lingua:BackwardRule or lingua:QueryRule.

A conjunctionList is a list with lingua:conjunction as first element and with
a rest list composed of zero or more subject predicate object 3 element triples.

A substitutionList is a list of (var:name value) pairs.

The lingua: prefix is <http://www.w3.org/2000/10/swap/lingua#> and is rooted
in the "Semantic Web Area for Play" http://www.w3.org/2000/10/swap/.

The var: prefix is <http://www.w3.org/2000/10/swap/var#> and is used for
variables that are interpreted as rule scoped universally quantified variables.
